===Etymology===
A later {{etyl|enm|en}} spelling, retaining the breathy {{m|enm|-s}}, of {{m|enm|hennes}}, ({{m|enm|henne}} + adverbial genitive ending {{m|enm|-s}}), from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|heonan||away", "hence}}, from a West Germanic root *hin- (compare Old Saxon [[hinan]], Old High German [[hinnan]], German [[hinnen]], Dutch [[heen]], Swedish [[hän]]); related to Old English {{m|ang|her||here}}.

